{"serial": "77025", "department_serial": 63, "code": "HK4027", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Business and Environmental Ethics", "ch": "企業與環境倫理"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Shih, Huei-Ying"], "ch": ["石慧瑩"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 5, "session": ["2", "3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "HK", "room": "104"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "客家語文暨社會科學學系", "en": "Department of Hakka Language and Social Sciences"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 30, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "企業是人?經濟活動上的重要發明，在充滿道德決定的日常生活中，企業作為當代社會重要的組織文化，其相關行為與所有人都有密不可分的關係，影響大眾權益甚深，不管你是雇主、員工、股東、上下游廠商、消費者或社區居民，企業的作為可說與全民息息相關，甚至改變自然環境。正由於企業與人們之間有重大關聯，這使得企業倫理成為當代應用倫理研究的重要領域。什麼是企業？企業的目的為何？企業對人、對自然生態有什麼樣的權利與義務？企業是否有社會責任？企業如何在追求利潤的過程中善盡保護環境的社會責任，都需要道德思辨歷程一一釐清。本課程除介紹企業與環境的倫理關係外，亦將適切地引用個案與實例作為討論的參照指標，藉此幫助同學理解企業倫理問題產生的根源及企業環境規範的必要性。", "en": "“In this course, we will examine a range of ethical issues arising as a result of the environmental impacts of business activities and practices. Among the questions that we will ask are: Is the natural world intrinsically valuable? If so, are businesses obligated to take this value into account when deciding whether to adopt potentially environmentally destructive practices? What are the implications of libertarian, free-market moral principles for the ethics of pollution-causing business activities? How should we understand the basis of our obligations to preserve the environment for future generations, and what are the implications for the practice of business? Are businesses that have contributed significantly to the threat of ecosystem (e.g. oil companies) obligated to contribute to environmental protection? More and more people believe that business leaders may be in the pursuit of profit but also lead the moral, to participate in the protection of future generations of the environment. Therefore, environmental responsibility can be an important strategy for enterprises to protect the environment not only to obtain the trust of consumers, employees and the community, but also get the respect of the national government.“"}, "outline": {"ch": "“ 什麼是企業倫理?\n 什麼是環境倫理?\n 企業的環境影響\n 企業對員工的倫理義務\n 企業對社區的倫理義務\n 企業與消費主義\n 企業對動物的倫理義務\n 企業對自然生態的倫理義務\n 企業的環境社會責任“", "en": "“What is business ethics?\nWhat is environmental ethics?\nThe environmental impact of business\nThe obligation of the corporation to employee\nThe obligation of the corporation to community\nThe corporation and consumerism\nThe obligation of the corporation to future generation\nThe obligation of the corporation to animals\nThe obligation of the corporation to ecosystem\nCSR and environmental responsibility“"}, "textbook": {"ch": "“葉保強著，《企業倫理》，五南，2008。", "en": "Peter Singer, Practical Ethics, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 1993.“"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "80", "en": "80"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "1.課堂參與、學習單20％ ; 2.課堂報告20％； 3.期中考30％ 4.期末考30％。", "en": "“Attendance and discussion 20％\nOral presentation 20％\nMid-term exam 30％\nFinal exam 30％“"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "週五上午8-9點", "en": "Friday 8-9AM"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "搭配課程設計，17、18兩週引導同學自行製作綠色生活筆記。", "en": "With course design, guide students to make green life notes by themselves in the last 2 weeks"}, "domain": {"ch": "社會思潮領域", "en": "社會思潮領域"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "具備客家語言文化的基本能力", "rating": "(1)非常低", "assesments": ["無"]}, {"competencies": "具備社會科學的學科能力", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "具備人文關懷的精神", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "具備掌握時勢脈動與創新發展的視野", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "口頭報告/口試",